        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Sikle</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> These things were great to me at 22. I would buff with shieldskin, shielding, banshee aura and spirit armor.  I would get a blue pet up, and buff him with focus death. My spell line up was like this:</P><P>Allure of Death<BR>Shieldskin<BR>Engulfing Darkness<BR>Siphon Life<BR>Focus Death<BR>Banshee Aura<BR>Leech<BR>Feign Death</P><P>After making sure I was fully buffed, I would pull with Leech, and let the pet bang on it while I tanked, and pounded on the Siphon Life key. I was doing 3 to 4 before I would have to med, and clearing the entire room in less than 5 minutes. The hard part is the two in the upper right hand corner that you cannot single pull. I saved them for last and medded to full and made sure to have full health before pulling them. I would let the pet tank one, and sl the other one til it died, then stepped in and killed the other one. I could usually end this fight with 40 mana and 60 health. Haven't had a chance to try the queen yet though. If any ran I would toss on an engulfing darkness. At 24 I switched out engulfing darkness for screaming terror, switched shielding for major shielding. </P><P>Hope that helps some. And no, I'm not twinked.</P><P>Knowledge is power. Power corrupts. Study hard. Be Evil.</font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Gunkk</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> re: getting Queen to pop.</P><P>In my experience, I found that I would get more Queens to pop when I could keep the room clear for at least a couple minutes before the Queen/PH pop.</P><P>This is nearly impossible without getting ST to land on the PH when doing the linked pull.</P><P>I would sit at the campsite (see Llorn's guide in my previous post for loc) clear the room as follows:  wanderer, rocks, middle, near-left, middle-left, far-left.  Starting from a full room, I could do this in &lt; 10 mins by my late 20s (untwinked).  This leaves the linked pair.</P><P>ST the PH/Queen and wait for the far-right Needlite to come to me -- do not sic pet yet.  You don't want the PH/Queen aggroing on the tanking pet.  Once it starts beating on you, then sic pet, step back, vortex, leach, and step back in.</P><P>If mem wipe sticks (usually did for me), then the spawn is broken and you can sit and med to full for almost 10 mins before taking the Queen/PH.</P><P>The spawn might be random and my experience might just be a conincidence, but I got a couple dozen queens to pop over 5 levels with this technique.  Gave away lots of stingers and gave/sold lots of wings.</P><P>On Nameless, there's a apparently a zone pathing bug that often has the wandering needlite popping near the bank & vendors.  So this makes holding the camp that much easier.</P><P>Happy Needlite Hunting!</P><P></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310159" target="_blank">Gunkk</a><BR>39 Iksar Necro<BR>The Nameless<BR></font></td>
